    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SSS scrambling formula in nr_generate_sss\n\n### Summary\nThe SSS generation function was using an incorrect formula for calculating the scrambling parameter m0. This caused the generated SSS sequences to not match the 3GPP TS 38.211 specification, leading to potential synchronization issues with UEs.\n\nThe issue was in the calculation where integer division was used instead of modulo operation, and the formula structure didn't match the specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_sss.c`: Corrected m0 calculation from `15*(Nid1/112) + (5*Nid2)` to `(15*Nid1 + Nid2) % 112`\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_sss.c`: Fixed debug section to properly define d_sss array\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running NR gNB with specific PCI values, the SSS sequences generated would not match expected patterns according to 3GPP specifications. This could be observed by capturing the over-the-air signals or by comparing generated sequences with reference implementations.\n\nUEs may fail to synchronize properly with the base station due to mismatched SSS sequences, particularly noticeable during initial cell search procedures.\n"
}